12/07/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki met with US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice on Tuesday (July 10th).
According to an official press release from Skopje, he was assured of US support for Macedonia's NATO aspirations.
Following the talks, Milososki said Rice also stressed the importance of reforming the judiciary, strengthening multiethnicity, and fighting corruption and crime.
He and Rice also discussed the Kosovo status issue and UN-mediated efforts to resolve Macedonia's longstanding name dispute with Greece.
(Vecer - 12/07/07;
MRT, Makfax, A1 TV - 11/07/07)
